Package com.markgrand.smileyvars

Class MapSetter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.markgrand.smileyvars.MapSetter
  • public class MapSetter
extends Object
    MapSetter is used to set the parameters of a SmileyVarsPreparedStatement from Maps that contain pairs of column names and values. You tell a MapSetter what SmileyVarsPreparedStatement method to use to set each column when the MapSetter is constructor. You do this by passing a map to the constructor that pairs column names with setter methods like this: 
         Map<String, BiSqlConsumer<SmileyVarsPreparedStatement, Object>> setterMap;
     setterMap.put("quantity", (svps, value) -> svps.setInt(svps, (int)value);
     setterMap.put("description", (svps, value) -> svps.setString(svps, (String)value);
     MapSetter mapSetter = new MapSetter(setterMap);

    Once the MapSetter is created, you can use it to do bulk updates like this:

         Collection<Map<String, Object>> records;
     SmileyVarsPreparedStatement svps;
     …
      for (Map<String, Object> record: records) {
          mapSetter.setSmileyVars(svps, record).executeUpdate();
      }
    Author:
    Mark Grand
